Add under a ## Build & Type Checking section near the top of CLAUDE.md\n\nAlways run `pnpm typecheck` (or `cd apps/web && pnpm tsc --noEmit`) from the `apps/web/` directory, NOT from the project root. Running from root produces thousands of false module resolution errors.
Add under a ## Editing Conventions section in CLAUDE.md\n\nWhen editing files, always read the file first to match exact indentation (tabs vs spaces) before using the Edit tool. If Edit fails twice due to whitespace mismatches, fall back to a full Bash write/sed approach immediately.
Add under a ## API & Validation section in CLAUDE.md\n\nThis project uses Zod v4 with oRPC. Key gotchas: avoid `.nullish()` (introduces null types that break oRPC serialization), use `.transform()` for optional fields, and ensure ORPCError is used instead of plain Error objects for proper error surfacing.
Add under a ## Debugging Workflow section in CLAUDE.md\n\nAfter fixing any bug, always check for related pre-existing issues that may be exposed (e.g., fixing a validation error may reveal a unique constraint bug). Run a quick smoke test of the full flow, not just the changed code path.
Add under a ## Internationalization section in CLAUDE.md\n\nTranslation files are in Arabic (ar) and English (en). When adding any new UI text, always add translations to BOTH locale files. Never leave translation keys missing.

